The attached wait-condition.json template can be used to verify the issue. For a timeout/rollback create the template and do nothing. For success create the template, look at the events to find the right URL and then manually satisfy the condition, e.g::

{code}
# curl -X PUT -H 'Content-Type:' --data-binary '{"Status" : "SUCCESS","Reason" : "Configuration Complete","UniqueId" : "ID1234","Data" : "Application has completed configuration."}' 'http://10.111.1.69:8773/services/objectstorage/cf-waitcondition-quggonjilgiqk/arn%3Aaws%3Acloudformation%3A%3A842396304075%3Astack/wait-condition/681ea889-28f7-4f0d-9296-86df261dc80d/myWaitHandle/WaitHandle?Expires=1419341033&AWSAccessKeyId=AKIRRZJLD5SN9V0TQ8CQ&x-amz-security-token=ZXVjYQABG3LGQX1Y%2BoWz8Mk%2FsBBqOd4XcrRlx0IpcLmRdYrM331dSXB76%2BKZ%2FTGUH8Tj3XL7INLTarxlg7%2BhFf6%2FBlLBwv77Y5X1Ka%2B1NBK2%2F%2BqaOpAdr9n7Vah4%2FRx0hZ8wAOnwgUdwKrvBSf9DmFsLixa8KPZdkmlqsVstmzfa1garrnrhF%2F8%2Fa2kOb7UmIy5PCK6Dhm0%2Fr30xPnbCZtHMLJSYOeIBr%2FASxihjFUCpTiiX69bEGViLWjLs7g%3D%3D&Signature=YLzMHQN%2FDHCO8zJ7iot0vYuj874%3D'
